Joyner-Kersee to Become Sixth Honorary Globetrotter
WASHINGTON , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- U.S. track star Jackie Joyner-Kersee will become the sixth honorary Harlem Globetrotter when the team stops in St. Louis on January 8.
Joyner-Kersee , who grew up in East St. Louis , and won two Olympic gold medals and a silver in the heptathlon before retiring this year , played college basketball at UCLA and professionally with the Richmond Rage of the recently defunct American Basketball League .
She joins basketball Hall of Famer Kareem Abdul-Jabbar , South African President Nelson Mandela , former Secretary of State Henry Kissinger , comedian Bob Hope and actress Whoopi Goldberg as honorary Globetrotters .
